You are auditing and hardening a PRODUCTION VoIP system (PRawwPlus). This is NOT a prototype. Treat it as a carrier-grade telecom backend.

Your goal is to identify and fix ALL bugs, vulnerabilities, race conditions, edge cases, and real-world failures — including unknown issues.

DO NOT rewrite the system. Perform a deep, systematic audit and apply minimal, targeted fixes.

⸻

🔴 SYSTEM CONTEXT

Stack:
	•	Node.js 20, Express 5, pnpm monorepo
	•	MongoDB (source of truth)
	•	FreeSWITCH (VoIP engine via ESL)
	•	React + React Native clients
	•	Firebase (auth + realtime UI only)
	•	PayFast (payments)

Architecture:
	•	FreeSWITCH = ONLY source of truth for call state
	•	Backend (CallOrchestrator) = ONLY source of truth for billing
	•	MongoDB = persistent truth
	•	Firebase = realtime display only

⸻

🔴 PHASE 1: STATIC CODE AUDIT

Identify:
	1.	Race conditions
	•	ESL events before DB writes
	•	Duplicate paths (ESL vs REST vs retry queue)
	2.	State machine violations
	•	Invalid transitions
	•	Missing terminal guards
	•	State overwrite risks
	3.	Billing vulnerabilities (CRITICAL)
	•	Double billing
	•	Missed billing
	•	Not using billsec
	•	Rounding errors
	4.	Data consistency
	•	MongoDB vs Firebase mismatch
	•	Non-atomic updates
	•	Missing transactions
	5.	UUID consistency
	•	FreeSWITCH UUID MUST equal DB callId everywhere
	6.	API reliability
	•	Missing timeouts
	•	Unhandled promise rejections
	•	Silent failures

⸻

🟠 PHASE 2: RUNTIME FAILURE ANALYSIS

Simulate:
	1.	Network failures
	•	Offline during call end
	•	API timeout
	•	ESL disconnect
	2.	Event anomalies
	•	Lost ESL events
	•	Duplicate events
	•	Out-of-order events
	3.	Concurrency
	•	Multiple calls per user
	•	Simultaneous balance updates
	•	Extension collisions
	4.	FreeSWITCH edge cases
	•	Missing CHANNEL_ANSWER
	•	Delayed CHANNEL_HANGUP_COMPLETE

⸻

🟡 PHASE 3: RELIABILITY HARDENING

Enforce:
	1.	Idempotency everywhere
	•	finalizeCall safe for multiple executions
	•	DB-level guards (not memory)
	2.	Event durability
	•	Replace dropped ESL events with MongoDB “pendingEvents”
	•	Add reconciliation worker
	3.	Billing correctness
	•	ONLY bill on CHANNEL_HANGUP_COMPLETE using billsec
	•	Atomic balance deduction
	4.	Strict state machine
	•	Reject invalid transitions
	•	Lock terminal states
	5.	UUID enforcement
	•	No mismatch allowed

⸻

🔐 PHASE 4: SECURITY HARDENING (CRITICAL)
	1.	FreeSWITCH security
	•	ESL = localhost or SSH tunnel only
	•	SIP restricted via ACL
	•	Strong credentials
	2.	Billing protection
	•	Max call duration
	•	Max spend per user/day
	•	Destination whitelist/blacklist
	3.	API protection
	•	Rate limiting (IP + user)
	•	Max concurrent calls
	4.	Fraud detection
	•	Detect rapid calls / expensive routes
	•	Auto-flag/block users
	5.	Auth security
	•	Password hashing
	•	Token expiry + refresh
	•	Brute-force protection
	6.	Secrets safety
	•	No secrets in repo
	•	Validate env usage

